        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 3:30PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 330 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Roxboro, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Roxboro, Concord, Bethel Hill, Hyco Lake, Mayo Reservoir, and Hyco
Marina.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
